1b:{"id":"youth-unemployment","categoryId":"unemployment","title":"Youth Unemployment (15–34)","value":"44.8%","rawValue":44.8,"unit":"%","change":-0.9,"changeLabel":"from Q3 2025","trend":"down","description":"Youth unemployment (ages 15–34) declined to 44.8% in Q4 2025. Among those aged 15–24, the rate stands at 61.4% — meaning roughly 6 in 10 young South Africans who want work cannot find it. South Africa's youth unemployment is among the highest globally.","source":"$1c","lastUpdated":"2026-02-17","series":"$1d"}
